<TITLE> Bangladesh asks WB, IMF for strings-free grants to LDCs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 16 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh has urged the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund to give increased, unconditional grants to the least developed countries (LDCs) to achieve the Millennium Development Goals. Ismat Jahan, permanent ambassador of Bangladesh to the United Nations, made the call in her address to a preparatory meeting on the follow-up conference on financing for development at the UN headquarters recently. The follow-up conference will be held from Nov 29 to Dec 2 in Qatar capital of Doha. "The international community should introduce a system which would allow the LDCs to borrow from international lenders at zero interest make-up against their own reserves," Jahan told the conference. Bangladesh as chair of the group of the LDCs said external debt burden greatly aggravated the poverty in the LDCs. She said all future debt to the LDCs should be provisional and grant-based without any conditionality. bd
